ol.li: Type Parity: The __u32 cross-definition ensures 4-byte fields on both 32-bit and 64-bit architectures. Using unsigned int would be ambiguous.
Struct Padding: Explicit _reserved field ensures the struct size (24B) doesn't change if the compiler applies different alignment rules across environments.
Direction Bits: _IOR encodes the 'Read' direction (Kernel -> User) identically because <linux/ioctl.h> and <sys/ioctl.h> share the same bit-shifting macros.
